class Solution {
public:
    bool check(vector<int>& nums) {
        int c = 0;
        int n = nums.size();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(nums[i]>nums[(i+1)%n])
                c++;
            if(c>1)
                return false;
        }
    return c<=1;
    }
};


Time Complexity :  O(n)
Space Complexity : O(1)

Approach 

1. Traverse the array.
2. Count how many times the current element is greater than the next element.
3. Use circular indexing: (i+1)%n
4. count ≤ 1 → array is sorted and rotated.
We will count the break point in a circular manner 
